    52	<objective>
    53	Emit `spectra_data` in the reference chunk struct (delta-encoded m/z) as the new default, with `--point`
    54	restoring the v1 point layout. Phase 2 chunks ONLY `spectra_data`: `spectra_peaks` stays point layout, and
    55	`chromatograms_data` stays point layout as an EXPLICIT, deliberate deviation from the reference (see below).
    56	Chunking is a fixed m/z window over the sorted m/z axis (default 50.0, `--chunk-size` configurable), one chunk
    57	row per non-empty window per spectrum, emitted through the Phase-1 streaming Handle as list columns. Phase 2
    58	applies NO zero-run nulling — chunked output decodes to the v1 point (m/z,intensity) multiset per spectrum,
    59	verified BITWISE (CHUNK-06; see verification for the exact/bounded decision procedure).
    60	
    61	Scope deviation (P1, documented): the authoritative reference `refs/mzPeak/small.chunked.mzpeak` emits
    62	`chromatograms_data` in CHUNK layout (time_chunk_start/end/values, chunk_encoding=MS:1003089, intensity,
    63	ms_level) — NOT point. Earlier CONTEXT/RESEARCH wrongly claimed the reference keeps chromatograms point; that
    64	claim is FALSE and is corrected here. Phase 2 deliberately keeps `chromatograms_data` POINT because the
    65	validator has no chromatogram structural rule and the TIC is tiny (chunking yields negligible size benefit).
    66	Full chromatogram chunking for complete structural parity is DEFERRED to Phase 5 (or a tracked follow-up).
    67	
    68	Purpose: smaller, reference-structured spectra_data without regressing v1 conformance or losslessness; lays
    69	the structure that Phase 3 (Numpress) and Phase 4 (ZRS null-marking) plug into.
    70	Output: a chunk codec + window chunker (with empty/all-equal/non-monotonic/singleton guards and a reference
    71	null-aware decoder), a `ChunkFacetStream`, a chunk `spectrum_array_index` footer, the `--point`/`--chunk-size`
    72	CLI flags, and NUnit locks covering codec round-trip, edge cases, reference-null decode, bitwise multiset
    73	equality, footer-parse lock, schema diff, validator 0/0 in both modes, and size shrink.
