   139	<task type="auto" tdd="true">
   140	  <name>Task 1: Chunk codec — null-aware delta encode/decode + fixed m/z-window chunker with edge-case guards + reference-null decode (no nulling in Phase 2)</name>
   141	  <files>ThermoRawFileParser/Writer/MzPeak/MzPeakChunkCodec.cs, ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/MzPeakChunkTests.cs</files>
   142	  <behavior>
   143	    Codec is null-aware in STRUCTURE (so it can READ reference / Phase-4 null-marked files) but Phase 2 NEVER
   144	    produces nulls in the writer path.
   145	    - DeltaEncode: given a window's m/z slice (no nulls in Phase 2), returns mz_chunk_start = first m/z,
   146	      mz_chunk_end = last m/z, mz_chunk_values = consecutive deltas of length (k-1) — the start value is NOT
   147	      in mz_chunk_values (it lives in mz_chunk_start). Mirror null_delta_encode: a value after a null is stored
   148	      ABSOLUTE, a leading null is kept as a marker. With no nulls this reduces to [mz[1]-mz[0], mz[2]-mz[1],...].
   149	    - DeltaDecode: given mz_chunk_start + mz_chunk_values, reconstructs the m/z array. Mirror null_delta_decode
   150	      byte-for-byte: start is the first reconstructed m/z; cumulative add for present deltas; absolute restart
   151	      after a null; nulls preserved aligned to intensity. Reconstructed (mz,intensity) drops pairs where either
   152	      is null. The decoder MUST correctly handle the reference leading-null cases (see Tests 5-6 below).
   153	    - Chunk(mz[], width): partition the sorted m/z axis into intervals each spanning <= width from the
   154	      interval's own first m/z (threshold = first_mz + width, advance by width; mirror null_chunk_every_k,
   155	      including: never emit a length-1 chunk — roll a singleton into the adjacent chunk; always emit the final
   156	      residual interval). Returns interval [start,end) index boundaries; one interval per non-empty window.
   157	    - Edge-case contract (P4), defined exactly and tested:
   158	      * EMPTY spectrum (k==0): Chunk returns zero intervals; the writer emits NO chunk row (mirror reference —
   159	        no empty/all-null chunk rows).
   160	      * ALL-EQUAL m/z chunk: every delta is 0.0; encode->decode reproduces the identical repeated value exactly.
   161	      * DESCENDING / NON-MONOTONIC m/z: the codec ASSUMES ascending sorted input (the per-scan path sorts).
   162	        Guard: if input is not non-decreasing, the chunker/encoder throws an explicit ArgumentException
   163	        (it does NOT silently produce a wrong layout). Document this contract; do not attempt to re-sort here.
   164	      * SPARSE BOUNDARY SINGLETON: a window that would close with a single point is rolled into the adjacent
   165	        chunk (length-1 chunks never emitted); the final residual singleton is folded into the previous chunk.
   166	    - Test 1 (round-trip, gapless): random sorted m/z + f32 intensity, chunk at 50.0, encode each window,
   167	      decode, concatenate -> decoded multiset is BITWISE-equal to input (DoubleToInt64Bits m/z keys + float
   168	      intensity bits), 0 mismatches.
   169	    - Test 2 (all-equal / duplicate m/z): input with repeated equal m/z survives encode->decode as the same
   170	      bitwise multiset (deltas of 0.0 reconstruct exactly).
   171	    - Test 3 (single-point spectrum): a 1-point m/z array yields one chunk, mz_chunk_values empty,
   172	      mz_chunk_start==mz_chunk_end==the point; decode returns exactly that point.
   173	    - Test 4 (empty + non-monotonic guards): empty input yields zero intervals and no chunk row; a
   174	      descending/non-monotonic input throws ArgumentException.
   175	    - Test 5 (reference null decode [None, absolute, delta]): hand-built mz_chunk_values starting
   176	      [None, <absolute m/z>, <delta>, ...] with aligned nullable intensity decodes with the null pair dropped,
   177	      the post-null value treated as an absolute restart, and subsequent deltas applied — reproducing the
   178	      RESEARCH worked example (row 1, spectrum 0). Proves the decoder reads reference / Phase-4 files.
   179	    - Test 6 (reference null decode [None, None] singleton-at-boundary): mz_chunk_values == [None, None]
   180	      decodes to a single peak at mz_chunk_start (mirror null_delta_decode's len>1 && arr[1] is None branch).
   181	  </behavior>
